    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>As the mother of a 6.5 month old that we are trying to decide how and when to introduce food to, I would like to express that I, at least, appreciate reading what you do and how you think about it.  In part because I identify with the sort of lax new-age-y attitude (I hope you don&#39;t find it offensive that I refer to it as lax) that everything will be okay, and in the last week I&#39;ve gotten overwhelmed (and confused…does introducing babies to solids really change how they absorb iron from breastmilk?) by reading perhaps too much on baby-led weaning (and perhaps by thinking about it too hard?).  So…thank you. 🙂  Also, thank you for your recipes, cause they&#39;re pretty awesome, and I quite enjoy your writing as well.  My baby boy *almost* let me make the cabbage risotto/soup yesterday, and though he didn&#39;t, really, (he HAD TO nurse THEN RIGHT THEN) it still turned out quite tasty.</p>
