    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I love this.  June seems very similar to our 17 month old daughter!  She also wasn&#39;t an early eater (had a persistent strong gag-reflex) and really wasn&#39;t swallowing any solid foods until after 12 months. Now she seems to enjoy mealtimes, but eats varying amounts (as you said, some days it&#39;s everything and then some, other days it&#39;s two  bites).  <br />I read this delightful article about giving kids sardines and tried her on the sardine butter recipe and she loves it! <a href="http://food52.com/blog/3419-the-sardine-that-saved-dinner" rel="nofollow ugc">http://food52.com/blog/3419-the-sardine-that-saved-dinner</a><br />So I&#39;ve been offering it at every meal and she usually has a few bites. She also loves eggs, beans and tea.  Loathes avocado 🙂</p>
