      <a href="https://orangette.net/2014/01/in-it-together/#comment-40985"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2014-01-16T16:08:18-05:00">Thursday, January 16, 2014 at 4:08 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Some kids eat all the things. Some do not. (Sam did. Truly doesn&#39;t. Well. She eats a goodly amount of popcorn but I don&#39;t think that really counts.) Our Dr., told me back when Sam was tiny to look at good in an arc of a week&#8211; did he eat meat this week? Check. Vegetables? Good. And if that meant tofu curry for three days in a row, fine. And cereal for the rest, we were good. As a young mom, the best examples I had were parents I admired with healthy kids running around with the occasional bags of Cheetos. Because really&#8211; it was going to be okay.</p>
    </div>

