  <li id="comment-41017" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://iheartkale.blogspot.com" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Hannah</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2014/01/in-it-together/#comment-41017"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2014-01-16T20:28:31-05:00">Thursday, January 16, 2014 at 8:28 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>&#8220;The way I see it, my job is to offer a reasonable variety of foods, the kind of stuff that Brandon and I eat, and June’s job is to choose which parts to eat and how much.&#8221;</p>
<p>YES.  I&#39;m assuming you&#39;ve read Ellyn Satter&#39;s &#8220;Child of Mine&#8221; book, which boils down to essentially that.  This is the division of labor I&#39;ve had with my two little ones (8 months and 3 years) and I wouldn&#39;t have it any other way.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-41017' data-commentid="41017" data-postid="221" data-belowelement="comment-41017" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Hannah" aria-label='Reply to Hannah'>Reply</a>    </div>
