    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I love reading your posts, no matter the topic.  I don&#39;t have children but have watched my twin nephews (now 6) develop their appetites since they could first eat solid food.  My sister started them early on things like plain yogurt, brussel sprouts and black beans, which they happily eat today.  What they like and don&#39;t like seems to constantly change.  Just watch the brussel sprouts though.  During one zoo day adventure, one got hidden in my car after a snack bag overturned.  Two days later the odor inside my car was nasty!!</p>
