  <li id="comment-41102" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/10559421117143224158" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Melissa</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2014/01/in-it-together/#comment-41102"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2014-02-17T19:17:28-05:00">Monday, February 17, 2014 at 7:17 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Thank you so much for deciding to write this post.  I am so happy to read that I am not alone in the fact that my son prefers to eat fruit, milk and meat (plus carbs).  Oh the meat eating, my son is a true carnivore.  He will even eat fish. <br />I love your whole approach to feeding June, I take the same approach but I didn&#39;t find the peace this approach brings until my son was about 13 months and stopped eating anything green. I fretted constantly over it, and I wish I had just let go sooner but I guess we all have to find our own way in our own time.  Thank you again, I really enjoyed reading this and seeing some pictures of June!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
